briefdescription.para: checks the state requests that are made.

detaileddescription.para: This function checks the validity of the state requests. The results of the checked is returned immediately.

simplesect.para: result of the state request that was made, taken from ILCK_RETURN_TYPE_e

detaileddescription.para: This function is used in the functioning of the ILCK state machine.

briefdescription.para: transfers the current state request to the state machine.

detaileddescription.para: This function takes the current state request from ilck_state and transfers it to the state machine. It resets the value from ilck_state to ILCK_STATE_NO_REQUEST

simplesect.para: retVal current state request, taken from ILCK_STATE_REQUEST_e

briefdescription.para: re-entrance check of ILCK state machine trigger function

detaileddescription.para: This function is not re-entrant and should only be called time- or event-triggered. It increments the triggerentry counter from the state variable ilck_state. It should never be called by two different processes, so if it is the case, triggerentry should never be higher than 0 when this function is called.

simplesect.para: retval 0 if no further instance of the function is active, 0xff else

briefdescription.para: Gets the latest value (TRUE, FALSE) the interlock was set to.

detaileddescription.para:
Meaning of the return value:
FALSE means interlock was set to be opened
TRUE means interlock was set to be closed

briefdescription.para: Reads the feedback pin of the interlock and returns its current value (ILCK_SWITCH_OFF/ILCK_SWITCH_ON)
Sets the interlock state to its requested state, if the interlock is at that time not in the requested state.

detaileddescription.para:
It returns E_OK if the requested state was successfully set or if the interlock was at the requested state before.

briefdescription.para: sets the current state request of the state variable ilck_state.

detaileddescription.para: This function is used to make a state request to the state machine,e.g, start voltage measurement, read result of voltage measurement, re-initialization It calls ILCK_CheckStateRequest() to check if the request is valid. The state request is rejected if is not valid. The result of the check is returned immediately, so that the requester can act in case it made a non-valid state request.
